Package model

Class State

java.lang.Object
model.State
public class State extends Object
This is the class for creating objects representing States that exist in the database. Each State has a stateId, name, Division, and DivisionId.

  • Constructor Details

    • State

      public State(int stateId, String stateName, String stateAbbreviation, int regionId)
      Constructor for instantiating State objects. This method pulls all the Regions from the database and then loops through them in order to assign the Region object that matches the regionId.
      Parameters:
      stateId - State ID as an int.
      stateName - State name as a string.
      stateAbbreviation - State abbreviation as a string.
      regionId - Region ID as an int.
